== Potato Dauphinoise ==

Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and cut @potatoes{2} into ½ cm thick rounds.

Add @water{125%ml}, @veg stock{1%sachet}, potatoes and @creme fraiche{110%g} to a #pot{}. Season with @salt{¼%tsp} and @pepper{¼%tsp}.

Bring to a boil, cover and simmer until parboiled, ~{12-18%mins}. Stir occasionally.

Transfer to an #oven dish{}. Scatter over @grated Italian style hard cheese{25%g} and @bacon lardons{100%g}. Place on a lined #baking tray{}. Cook on the middle shelf for ~{15-20%mins}.

== Roasted Vegetables ==

Meanwhile, trim the @carrot{1} and @parsnip{1} and halve lengthways. Chop into 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pop onto a lined baking tray.

Toss with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Roast on the top shelf until tender, ~{20-25%mins}.

Meanwhile, trim the bottom of the @broccolini{75%g}. Halve thick stems lengthways.

When the veg has 10 mins left to cook, add the broccolini to the tray. Toss with salt, pepper and a drizzle of oil. Cook until tender, ~{10-12%mins}.

== Hazelnut Crusted Turkey ==

Meanwhile, finely chop the @hazelnuts{10%g}.

Beat @egg{1} in a #bowl{}.

Add the @breadcrumbs{1%pack} and nuts to another bowl. Season with @salt{½%tsp} and @pepper{to taste}.

Dip the @Irish turkey breast{1} first in the egg and then the breadcrumbs. Ensure it's completely coated. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw turkey and its packaging.

Once coated, transfer to a clean #plate{}.

Place a #pan{} over high heat with enough @oil{to taste} to coat the bottom.

Once hot, carefully lay the turkey into the pan.

Reduce the heat to medium-high and fry until golden brown, ~{2-3%mins} on each side.

Transfer the turkey to the baking tray with the potatoes.

Roast on the middle shelf of the oven until cooked through, ~{8-10%mins}. IMPORTANT: Turkey is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Cranberry Butter Sauce ==

Wipe the pan used to fry the turkey and return to medium-high heat.

Add the @cranberry chutney{1%sachet} and @water{50%ml} and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%mins}.

Once thickened, stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted and combined.

== To Serve ==

Share the hazelnut crusted turkey between plates.

Drizzle over the cranberry butter sauce.

Serve the broccolini, carrot and bacon dauphinoise alongside.